President Donald J. Trump has appointed Lieutenant General Herbert Raymond "H.R." McMaster as Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs. McMaster is a West Point graduate and holds a Ph.D from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. He has served in the United States Army for over three decades, playing key roles in operations such as Operation Iraqi Freedom, Operation Enduring Freedom, and the Gulf War. McMaster has received the Silver Star for his valor during the Gulf War. Prior to his appointment, he served as Director of the Army Capabilities Integration Center and as Deputy Commanding General, Futures at the U.S. Army Training and Doctrine Command. President Trump stated that McMaster's experience and knowledge will be valuable in protecting America's interests at home and abroad. McMaster expressed his commitment to the safety and security of the American people in his new role.